04/04/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu has undergone successful prostate surgery at the military hospital in Ankara, according to an official statement from Tirana on Monday (3 April). Moisiu, 76, has been in the Turkish capital since 29 March for tests. It is still unclear when he will be released. 
In other news, after two previous failed attempts, the Albanian Parliament finally endorsed a law Monday imposing a three-year ban on the private possession and circulation of speedboats. Prime Minister Sali Berisha had urged deputies to pass the law, calling it a weapon in the fight against trafficking and organised crime. (Albanian News - 04/04/06)
